U-Pay privacy policy
General terms
The terms and conditions of this article will be the "agreement" between you and U-Pay Digital Plc. The use of
      "U-Pay
      Wallet" will be governed by this agreement. This article is the general terms and conditions above any specific
      product
      terms, fees, charges and information shown in our promotional and marketing materials.
By clicking on your device to agree and accept these terms and conditions, you confirm that you have read,
      understood
      and agree to all the terms, conditions and tips contained in this agreement, and this agreement is between you and
      U-Pay
      Digital Plc. Produce legal effect.
In this agreement, "customer", "you", "your" and "your own" refer to the owner of a wallet account that can be
      accessed
      using a mobile device. "We", "our" and "U-Pay" refer to U-Pay Digital Plc.
We are well aware of the importance of personal information to you, and will do our best to protect your personal
      information safe and reliable. We are committed to maintaining your trust in us and abide by the following
      principles to
      protect your personal information: consistent rights and responsibilities, clear purpose, choice and consent,
      minimum
      sufficient, security, subject participation, openness and transparency, etc. At the same time, we promise that we
      will
      adopt corresponding security protection measures to protect your personal information in accordance with the
      mature
      security standards of the industry.
If you have any complaints and reports about personal information security, or if you have any questions,
      comments
      or
      suggestions about this policy or U-Pay's privacy measures, please contact us (contact email: inquiry@u-pay.com
      -Leave a message on our Facebook page to @upay.kh
      -Premium payment hotline: 085-978-899 (Khmer/English); 081-978-899 (Khmer/Chinese)).
U-Pay and its affiliates (hereinafter referred to as "us"), as the operators of U-Pay, are well aware of the
      importance
      of personal information to you, and we will protect your personal information and privacy in accordance with laws
      and
      regulations. We have formulated this "Privacy Policy" and specially reminded: We hope you read and understand this
      privacy policy carefully before using U-Pay and related services in order to make appropriate choices.
This privacy policy will help you understand:
We will collect and use your information in accordance with the privacy policy, but we will not collect
        personal
        information in a mandatory bundle just because you agree to this privacy policy.
When you use or turn on related functions or use services, we will collect and use relevant information in
        order
        to
        realize the functions and services necessary. Unless it is necessary for the realization of basic business
        functions or
        in accordance with the requirements of laws and regulations, you can refuse to provide without affecting other
        functions
        or services. We will explain what is necessary information item by item in the privacy policy.
You have logged in to your account, and we will push information based on the account information.
In order to help you find more friends, we may apply for address book permissions.
We respect your right to choose. If you don't want to be recommended to friends, you can turn it off at any
        time
        in
        "Me-Settings-Privacy Settings".
The address book, precise geographic location, camera, microphone, and album permissions will not be turned on
        by
        default. Only after your express authorization can they be used for specific functions or services, and you can
        also
        withdraw authorization. In particular, we need to point out that even if we have obtained these sensitive
        permissions
        with your authorization, we will not collect your information when the relevant functions or services are not
        needed.
This privacy policy applies to your access and use of our products and services through U-Pay, U-Pay software
        development kit (SDK) and application programming interface (API) for third-party websites and applications.
The following will help you understand in detail how we collect, use, store, transfer, share, transfer (if
      applicable)
      and protect personal information; help you understand the ways to query, access, delete, correct, and withdraw
